[normal]Written evidence from [bold]Agricultural Biotechnology Council ([bold]abc[bold]) [bold]The views expressed in this submission are those of 
[normal]abc
[normal] - the umbrella organisation for the agricultural biotechnology industry in the 
[normal]UK
[normal]. 
[normal]abc
[normal], comprising of six member companies, works with the food chain and research community to invest in a broad range 
[normal]of crop technologies â€“ including conventional and advanced breeding techniques, such as GM.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] These are designed to 
[normal]promote the sustainable intensification of agriculture
[normal] by tackling challenges such as pests, diseases and changing climatic conditions
[normal],
[normal] whilst reducing water usage, greenhouse gas emissions and other inputs.
[normal] 
[normal]The companies are BASF, Bayer, Dow, Monsanto, Pioneer (DuPont) and 
[normal]Syngenta
[normal].
